1 2. a. It is necessary that the powers conferred on the Board
2 by the Oklahoma Veterinary Practice Act be construed
3 to protect the health, safety and welfare of the
4 people of this state.
5 b. No member of the Board, acting in that capacity or as
6 a member of any Board committee, shall participate in
7 the making of any decision or the taking of any action
8 affecting such member's own personal, professional or
9 pecuniary interest, or that of a person related to the
10 member within the third degree by consanguinity,
11 marriage or adoption or of a business or professional
12 associate.
13 c. With advice of legal counsel, the Board shall adopt
14 and annually review a conflict of interest policy to
15 enforce the provisions of the Oklahoma Veterinary
16 Practice Act.
17 C. The practice of veterinary medicine is a privilege granted
18 by the people of this state acting through their elected
19 representatives. It is not a natural right of individuals. In the
20 interest of the public, and to protect the public, it is necessary
21 to provide laws and rules to govern the granting and subsequent use
22 of the privilege to practice veterinary medicine. The primary
23 responsibility and obligation of the Board is to protect the public
24
